OL,3,CMichael Gove insists the government
OL,4,Cwill ban no fault evictions before
OL,5,Celection
OL,7,Fhas insisted the government will ban
OL,8,Fno fault evictions before the next
OL,9,Felection, despite continuous delays to
OL,10,Fthe plan.JThe Conservative Party
OL,11,Fmanifesto in 2019 pledged to ban
OL,12,FSection 21 - which allows landlords to
OL,13,Fevict tenants without having to give a
OL,14,Freason outside of a tenancy agreement
OL,15,F- but the legislation still hasn't
OL,16,Fbeen passed to outlaw it.JHousing
OL,17,Fcharities and campaigners have told
OL,18,FITV News they fear the ban is being
OL,19,Fquietly removed or watered down in the
OL,20,FRenters Reform Bill currently going
OL,21,Fthrough Parliament.JITV News has been
OL,22,Finvestigating the evictions crisis for
OL,23,Fthe past 12 months and found working
OL,24,Ffamilies being kicked out of their
OL,25,Fhomes with just 8 weeks notice,
OL,26,Fdespite never missing a rent payment
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/4
