OL,3,CMichael Gove insists the government
OL,4,Cwill ban no fault evictions before
OL,5,Celection
OL,7,FThe Housing Secretary however gave a
OL,8,Fguarantee on the BBC's Kuenssberg
OL,9,Fprogramme that Section 21 will be
OL,10,Foutlawed this year. He said it was
OL,11,Fvital to make sure unscrupulous
OL,12,Flandlords aren't allowed to use the
OL,13,Fpractice to raise rents and evict good
OL,14,Ftenants who report legitimate
OL,15,Fproblems.JBut Michael Gove faces
OL,16,Fsignificant opposition from within his
OL,17,Fown party with Conservative MPs - some
OL,18,Fof whom are also landlords - pushing
OL,19,Fhard against the plans.JThere also
OL,20,Fappears to be less enthusiasm for the
OL,21,Freforms beyond Mr Gove's department,
OL,22,Fwith a view within DLUHC that Downing
OL,23,FStreet does not necessarily view the
OL,24,Flegislation as a key priority in an
OL,25,Felection year. The department is
OL,26,Fpushing hard get it through.JMr Gove
